                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Phelon</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/24/2003&nbsp;: 04:46:59 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Tradeskilling is generaly not the money making machine people think it is.  Sure if you have 250 in smithing or tailoring and have the right diety you can make moer than it cost you to get there.  But but these are not easy skills to get.  And the easy skills to master have 100 other people on your server churning out the same ole junk and flooding the market.<br /><br />My advice for cash is LoY.  With the group you described you can hold a decent size ship in dulak or head to nadox.  With the plat and gems you get some cash, and the drops will either equip you or fund you even more.  Or hit up some of the forgotten Kunark zones.  HS is almost always empty.<br /><br />And one thing that you can always rely on is the laziness of a raiding high lvl.  I'm only 59, but I'd rather pay someone else for dorf heads/milita helms/salts and skins then waste my time farming them myself when I need the faction.  Alot of your tradeskillers need various items to make this uber deity stuff, find out the things they might need that is mindless farming for a 65th char.  Good example of that is the rockhoppers in DP, your group will still get xp there and the pelt can sell for up to 100pp each, maybe more.<br /><br />But ultimately there are very few places you can get great coin without doing something fairly repetitive.  Just change it up, find a few cash spots you can do for a session aand rotate the ones you do.  This also helps when one of your spots in camped you have something you can move on to.<br /><br />Hope something here helps.  gl luck in your search for the phat coinage.</span></font></td>
